caption: Great food!

Honestly the first time in years I felt I was ripped off. I asked for beef stew six dollars for a small, they were out. I asked for a recommendation and she gave me Oxtail which she said only came in med and large, I got the medium. It came on rice with a side of yams. There was enough meat to fill maybe two tablespoons, the rest was fat. It had no taste whatsoever, everything on the plate had no flavor. To top it all off they charged me 17 dollars lol, I had to do a double take. After a few bites I tossed it all in the garbage, I'll make it up to myself tonight with some good Chinese food.

Not sure why this place is still in business. I order a stew chicken with rice and peas, the food was just thrown into the box by the time i got home the bag was a mess completely turned me off from eating. I am from a jamaican heritage and this is one Jamaican business i will no lo ger support. Waste of my money thank god there are places to eat in that neighborhood. They display one price and then tell you another price when you ready to pay. Beside i order stew chicken but got more like stew chicken back. Definitely will not be going back not worth my money

The jerk chicken tasted like barbecue chicken with a sauce, the fry chicken needed  more seasoning like some maggi. The presentation was horrible.  The  steam vegetables and the meat should be in one container, gravy & rice should be a separate container. The oxtail and the rice was the best tasting thing. The plantain was cut too thick and they were very dry. The food was swimming in gravy.

Little Ochie has good authentic Jamaican food.  Lots of dishes to choose from.  Portions fill you up but if you get a large depends on the type of meat you order it's not a match to the price.  They serve more rice than anything.   I expect that if I buy large I'm able to share with one or two people at least the meat should be equal to share.  Star lost for that plus the non-friendly customer service..
